1. Write a JAVA method to print multiplication table of a number n

Code : 

public class practice {
    static void multiply(int n){
        System.out.println("Multiplication of the number : "+n+"\n");
        for(int i=1 ; i<11 ; i++){
            int mul = n*i;
            System.out.println("\t"+n+"X"+i+"="+mul);
        }
    }
    public static void main(String[] args){
        multiply(5);
    }
}

Output : 

Multiplication of the number : 5

	5X1=5
	5X2=10
	5X3=15
	5X4=20
	5X5=25
	5X6=30
	5X7=35
	5X8=40
	5X9=45
	5X10=50

